CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 11, 1941, pg. 8 reads: "Officials In Local YWCA Drive Take Counsel - The annual campaigning for the YWCA Budget opens Monday. Here are pictured the officials of the Centre Avenue Branch discussing the branch's goal of $3000.  They are, left to right: Mrs. Henry Parker, Miss Irene Boozer, executive secretary: Mrs. J.A. Wayts, Mrs. Arthur W. Taylor, chairman: Mrs. Walter Brice, Mrs. Robert Thompson.  Other leaders not pictured: Mrs. Earl Hord, Mrs. Edward Lampkins, Mrs. William Cuthbert. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait from left: Mrs. Henry Parker, Irene Boozer, Mrs. J. A. Wayts, Mrs. Arthur W. Taylor, Mrs. Walter Brice, and Mrs. Robert Thompson, seated around wooden table in Centre Avenue YWCA for annual campaign budget meeting
